#Text=Larsson goal puts United into quarterfinals
#Text=Wednesday , March 7 , 2007
#Text=Manchester United 1(2 ) 0(0 )
#Text=Lille OSC
#Text=Match Stats
#Text=Attendance 75182
#Text=Goalscorers for Manchester United
#Text=Larsson ( 72 ' )
#Text=Goalscorers for Lille OSC
#Text=None
#Text=Bookings ( Manchester United )
#Text=Ronaldo , Richardson ( Yellow ( 2 ) )
#Text=Bookings ( Lille OSC )
#Text=Makoun , Chalme , Tafforeau , Plestan ( Yellow ( 4 ) )
#Text=Manchester United progressed to the quarterfinals of the Champions League earlier today after defeating Lille 1-0 for the second time .
#Text=After the controversial winning goal from the first leg , United had a strong advantage in the series , and Lille needed a win to advance .
#Text=The scorer of that controversial goal , Ryan Giggs , was left out of the lineup , and instead the more defensive minded John O'Shea was played .
#Text=Lille started the game with a defensive lineup as well , hoping to stall the Red Devils , and make a score later in the match .

#Text=Manchester United came into the game short of several key players due to injury , including Louis Saha ( hamstring ) , Ole Gunnar Solsjkaer ( surgery recovery ) , and Darren Fletcher ( ankle ) .
#Text=Striker Alan Smith was on the bench for United hoping to get back to first team action after a broken leg kept him out of the main squad for nearly a year .

#Text=United grabbed the first of the chances 15 minutes into the game after Scholes popped in a cross to Rooney , but the young striker could n't get his volley away in time , and Mathieu Chalme moved well to block .
#Text=The ensuing corner saw another good chance present itself for United , but John O'Shea 's powerful headed from Carrick 's kick hit only the crossbar .
#Text=Lille then had a chance of their own as Makoun strafed in behind the defence to connect with a freekick by Obraniak .
#Text=Makoun 's header was poor , and keeper Edwin Van Der Sar had and easy time collecting the ball .
#Text=When Macnhester United earned themselves a freekick outside the Lille area , two Lille players placed themselves directly in front of Paul Scholes , not allowing him to take an early kick .
#Text=Lille was appearing to be playing stronger , and made quick moves on the counter attack to worry United .
#Text=One fine pass by Chalme into the box was aimed for a wide open Odemwingie , but he was not able to cleanly hit the ball , and the danger passed .
#Text=Cristiano Ronaldo made his presence felt in the Lille area and was brought down by Chalme in the box .
#Text=Instead of a penalty , Ronaldo was awarded a yellow card for what referee Luis Cantalejo considered a dive .
#Text=The second half saw Lille continue to dominate the football match , and the first threat came through a long range shot by Keita , but Van Der Sar saved well .
#Text=Odemwingie was again on the attack , but was unfortunate to see his header smash off the post .
#Text=United finally had a chance of their own in the second half when defender Nemanja Vidic connected with a free kick by Rooney , but the Serbian 's header flew just over the goal .
#Text=A sense of anxiety was starting to fill Old Trafford until Ronaldo and Larsson combined to put the series away after 72 minutes .
#Text=Ronaldo used some of his trademark moves to outwit 3 Lille defenders and knocked a well aimed ball into Larsson , who forced a powerful header into the back of the net .
#Text=The goal will be the last Larsson will score for United at Old Trafford , as his loan contract expires on the 12th of March .
#Text=Larsson was applauded as he left the pitch and was replaced by Alan Smith , who was eager to impress after his extended absence from the team .
#Text=Lille made two changes of their own , throwing Fauvergue and Mirallis into the fray , but they never looked likely to get the two goals they needed to advance .
#Text=United went on to win , but now have even more injury worries as Mikael Silvestre had to be stretchered off the field after sustaining a head injury .
